Objective: implement order lifecycle with states {PENDING, PROCESSING, COMPLETED, CANCELLED}, controlled transitions, scheduler-driven PENDING→PROCESSING, validation, caching, logging, tests, and OpenAPI.

APIs: POST /orders, GET /orders[?status], GET /orders/{id}, PATCH /orders/{id}/status.

Scheduler: configurable poll interval and batch size; promotes orders when scheduledProcessingAt<=now; idempotent; transactional with optimistic locking (@Version).

Persistence: Spring Data JPA; H2 default. Cache: cache reads, evict on updates. Errors: return JSON with appropriate 400/404/409/500.

Tests: unit (services), controller (MockMVC), integration (H2 + scheduler). Build/run/test: mvn -f Order-engine clean package; mvn -f Order-engine spring-boot:run; mvn -f Order-engine test.

Config keys: app.scheduler.enabled, app.scheduler.poll-interval-seconds, app.scheduler.promotion-batch-size, app.cache.ttl-seconds.

